author: Jenny Hsu
title: Crude Prices Steady in Asia
text: 0225 GMT [Dow Jones] Crude oil prices are largely stagnant in Asia as traders hesitate to take long positions due to persistent oversupply amid sputtering demands, says ANZ Research, saying it expects commodity prices to stay low for the reminder of the year. “Speculators are cutting bets on rising oil prices. Net speculative (U.S.) long positions declined by 13,841 contracts for the week ending 20 October,” the research notes.
